document_data.History:
[[Zhengyi the Witch-King]] used Helmsdale as his base of operations beginning during the [[Vaasan War]] with his forces being fully expelled before the end of the {{YearlinkName|1359}}, with the help of forces from [[Ironspur]].

Because of the town's longstanding association with Zhengyi's [[undead]] forces, many Damarans often referred to Helmsdale as "the cursed village" in the mid 14{{th}} century [[DR]].

In the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]], Helmsdale was home to one of the former wives of King [[Yarin Frostmantle]]. After she bore a daughter following her split with the king, the spiteful monarch ordered the child to be killed. She was saved by the intervention of [[Showithal Terdidy]], a member of the [[Kneebreakers]], who subsequently fled the realm to avoid the king's wrath.{{Cite digital book/Hero/Kindle||13}}
